  "slug": "roast-leg-of-pork",
  "title": "Roast Leg of Pork",
  "subtitle": "A traditional Sunday joint with sage and onion stuffing and proper crackling",
  "excerpt": "Leg of pork is larger and leaner than shoulder, making it the classic slicing joint for a formal Sunday table. Bone-in or boned and rolled, it roasts in 2-3 hours and delivers clean, slightly firmer slices alongside the obligatory crackling.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Mrs Beeton, Book of Household Management (1861), Project Gutenberg #10136: roasting leg of pork with sage stuffing. Eliza Acton, Modern Cookery for Private Families (1845): sage and onion forcemeat. Traditional British Sunday lunch practice.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A bone-in leg of pork is a substantial joint that suits a larger gathering. Unlike shoulder, which benefits from very long, slow cooking, the leg has less fat marbling and cooks more quickly at a moderate temperature. The result is firmer, cleaner slices with a crust of salt-blistered crackling on top.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The traditional accompaniment is sage and onion ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "forcemeat",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpdr2umm0000ygv4v2dex3c7"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ", baked in a separate dish and served in spoonfuls alongside. Some households stuff it into the cavity if the butcher has boned the leg; others bake it separately for a crispier top.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What you need",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
